  "prompt": "These days, I feel like thousand things are running into my mind at one time. I can't sleep peacefully at night as many things keep flashing back. Sometimes, I find myself engaged in imaginary talks with me and I also feel restlessness. Is this all happening because I am stressed?",
  "response": "Based on your description, it sounds like you may be experiencing symptoms of stress, anxiety, or overthinking. Here are some insights and suggestions:\n\nPotential Causes:\n1. High stress levels\n2. Anxiety\n3. Overthinking\n4. Work or personal life pressures\n5. Unresolved emotional issues\n6. Lack of mental relaxation\n\nSymptoms You're Experiencing:\n- Racing thoughts\n- Difficulty sleeping\n- Imaginary conversations\n- Mental restlessness\n- Constant mental activity\n\nRecommended Strategies:\n1. Stress Management\n- Practice meditation\n- Deep breathing exercises\n- Regular physical exercise\n- Yoga\n- Mindfulness techniques\n\n2. Mental Health Support\n- Talk to a counselor or therapist\n- Share your feelings with trusted friends/family\n- Consider professional psychological help\n\n3. Sleep Hygiene\n- Maintain a consistent sleep schedule\n- Create a calm bedtime routine\n- Avoid screens before sleeping\n- Practice relaxation techniques\n- Use calming music or white noise\n\n4. Cognitive Techniques\n- Journal your thoughts\n- Practice cognitive behavioral techniques\n- Challenge negative thought patterns\n- Learn to live in the present moment\n\nIf symptoms persist or worsen, consulting a mental health professional is recommended.",
